## 2. Background — What Tranche 2 Is Expected to Require

Based on the Attorney-General's Department consultations, the OAIC's forward guidance, and the AI6 Guidance for AI Adoption (October 2024), Tranche 2 is anticipated to include the following:

| Anticipated Requirement | Description | Likelihood |
|------------------------|------------|------------|
| High-risk AI classification | Mandatory identification and classification of AI systems that pose significant risk to individuals | High |
| Conformity assessment | Independent assessment of high-risk AI systems against safety, fairness, and transparency standards | High |
| Mandatory AI register | Organisations must maintain and, in some cases, publish a register of AI systems in use | High |
| Enhanced transparency | Individuals must be informed when AI is used in decisions that affect them, with explanation of logic | High |
| Algorithmic impact assessments | Mandatory impact assessments for AI systems with significant effects on individuals | Medium-High |
| Human oversight requirements | Mandated human review for specified categories of automated decisions | Medium |
| AI incident reporting | Mandatory reporting of AI-related incidents (bias events, safety failures, rights impacts) | Medium |
| Extraterritorial reach | Requirements applied to overseas AI providers processing Australians' data | Medium |

