## 3. High-Risk AI System Identification

### 3.1 Identification Criteria

{{ business_name }} must assess each AI system against the following criteria to determine if it is likely to be classified as high-risk under Tranche 2:

| Criterion | High-Risk Indicator | {{ business_name }} Assessment |
|-----------|--------------------|-----------------------------|
| Decision impact | AI makes or materially assists decisions affecting individuals' legal rights, access to services, employment, credit, insurance, or housing | To be assessed per system |
| Vulnerability of subjects | AI processes data of children, elderly persons, persons with disability, or First Nations peoples | To be assessed per system |
| Scale | AI affects a large number of individuals | To be assessed per system |
| Reversibility | AI decisions are difficult or impossible to reverse | To be assessed per system |
| Autonomy | AI operates with limited or no human oversight | To be assessed per system |
| Data sensitivity | AI processes sensitive information as defined by the Privacy Act | To be assessed per system |

