## 8. Implementation Timeline

| Phase | Activities | Target Completion |
|-------|-----------|-------------------|
| **Phase 1 — Foundation** (Months 1-3) | Complete AI system inventory; classify all systems against high-risk criteria; conduct gap analysis; secure senior leadership endorsement | {{ effective_date }} + 3 months |
| **Phase 2 — Critical Gaps** (Months 3-6) | Conduct PIAs for high-risk systems; implement human oversight mechanisms; establish AI incident register; negotiate vendor DPAs and audit rights | {{ effective_date }} + 6 months |
| **Phase 3 — Compliance Build** (Months 6-9) | Implement transparency and disclosure mechanisms; establish bias testing programme; build comprehensive AI register; map overseas data flows | {{ effective_date }} + 9 months |
| **Phase 4 — Assessment Readiness** (Months 9-12) | Engage conformity assessor for pre-assessment; conduct internal audit against anticipated requirements; remediate identified gaps; prepare evidence packages | {{ effective_date }} + 12 months |
| **Phase 5 — Monitoring** (Ongoing) | Monitor Attorney-General's Department announcements; adjust plan as Tranche 2 details are confirmed; maintain continuous compliance | Ongoing |

